{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "The Hurtful Tongue"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Hear, O God, my voice of complaint; preserve my life from dread of the enemy."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Hide me from the scheming of the wicked, from the mob of workers of iniquity,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "who sharpen their tongues like swords and aim their bitter words like arrows,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "ambushing the innocent in seclusion, shooting suddenly, without fear."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They hold fast to their evil purpose; they speak of hiding their snares."
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Who will see them?",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "they say."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They devise injustice and say,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "We have perfected a secret plan.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For the inner man and the heart are mysterious."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But God will shoot them with arrows; suddenly they will be wounded."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They will be made to stumble, their own tongues turned against them.\nAll who see will shake their heads."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Then all mankind will fear and proclaim the work of God;\nso they will ponder what He has done."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let the righteous rejoice in the LORD and take refuge in Him;\nlet all the upright in heart exult."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}